{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":394,"text":"\"Give me liberty or give me death.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":3999,"text":"When Patrick Henry, the governor of Virginia,"},{"time":6266,"text":"said these words in 1775,"},{"time":9191,"text":"he could never have imagined"},{"time":11094,"text":"just how much they would come to resonate"},{"time":13159,"text":"with American generations to come."},{"time":16182,"text":"At the time, these words were earmarked"},{"time":18847,"text":"and targeted against the British,"},{"time":21220,"text":"but over the last 200 years, they've come to embody"},{"time":24119,"text":"what many Westerners believe,"},{"time":26807,"text":"that freedom is the most cherished value,"},{"time":30255,"text":"and that the best systems of politics and economics"},{"time":33176,"text":"have freedom embedded in them."},{"time":35390,"text":"Who could blame them?"},{"time":37184,"text":"Over the past hundred years, the combination"},{"time":40098,"text":"of liberal democracy and private capitalism"},{"time":43141,"text":"has helped to catapult the United States"},{"time":45561,"text":"and Western countries"},{"time":46822,"text":"to new levels of economic development."},{"time":49235,"text":"In the United States over the past hundred years,"},{"time":51953,"text":"incomes have increased 30 times,"},{"time":54343,"text":"and hundreds of thousands of people"},{"time":56014,"text":"have been moved out of poverty."},{"time":58287,"text":"Meanwhile, American ingenuity and innovation"},{"time":62320,"text":"has helped to spur industrialization"},{"time":65699,"text":"and also helped in the creation and the building"},{"time":68561,"text":"of things like household appliances"},{"time":70352,"text":"such as refrigerators and televisions,"},{"time":72575,"text":"motor vehicles and even the mobile phones in your pockets."},{"time":76623,"text":"It's no surprise, then, that even at the depths"},{"time":79305,"text":"of the private capitalism crisis,"},{"time":81569,"text":"President Obama said,"},{"time":83336,"text":"\"The question before us is not whether the market"},{"time":86232,"text":"is a force for good or ill."},{"time":88867,"text":"Its power to generate wealth and to expand freedom"},{"time":92090,"text":"is unmatched.\""},{"time":94168,"text":"Thus, there's understandably"},{"time":96057,"text":"a deep-seated presumption among Westerners"},{"time":99191,"text":"that the whole world will decide to adopt"},{"time":102001,"text":"private capitalism as the model of economic growth,"},{"time":105085,"text":"liberal democracy, and will continue"},{"time":107392,"text":"to prioritize political rights over economic rights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111523,"text":"However, to many who live in the emerging markets,"},{"time":114373,"text":"this is an illusion, and even though"},{"time":117337,"text":"the Universal Declaration of Human Rights,"},{"time":119444,"text":"which was signed in 1948,"},{"time":121715,"text":"was unanimously adopted,"},{"time":124010,"text":"what it did was to mask a schism"},{"time":126701,"text":"that has emerged between developed\nand developing countries,"},{"time":130224,"text":"and the ideological beliefs"},{"time":132305,"text":"between political and economic rights."},{"time":135952,"text":"This schism has only grown wider."},{"time":139489,"text":"Today, many people who live in the emerging markets,"},{"time":142059,"text":"where 90 percent of the world's population lives,"},{"time":144972,"text":"believe that the Western obsession"},{"time":147000,"text":"with political rights is beside the point,"},{"time":149627,"text":"and what is actually important"},{"time":151605,"text":"is delivering on food, shelter,"},{"time":153826,"text":"education and healthcare."},{"time":155924,"text":"\"Give me liberty or give me death\""},{"time":158340,"text":"is all well and good if you can afford it,"},{"time":161103,"text":"but if you're living on less than one dollar a day,"},{"time":164066,"text":"you're far too busy trying to survive"},{"time":166034,"text":"and to provide for your family"},{"time":167850,"text":"than to spend your time going around"},{"time":169381,"text":"trying to proclaim and defend democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172392,"text":"Now, I know many people in this room"},{"time":174239,"text":"and around the world will think,"},{"time":176427,"text":"\"Well actually, this is hard to grasp,\""},{"time":179410,"text":"because private capitalism and liberal democracy"},{"time":182637,"text":"are held sacrosanct."},{"time":184903,"text":"But I ask you today, what would you do"},{"time":187272,"text":"if you had to choose?"},{"time":189083,"text":"What if you had to choose"},{"time":190897,"text":"between a roof over your head"},{"time":193360,"text":"and the right to vote?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":195037,"text":"Over the last 10 years,"},{"time":196630,"text":"I've had the privilege to travel to over 60 countries,"},{"time":200410,"text":"many of them in the emerging markets,"},{"time":202615,"text":"in Latin America, Asia,"},{"time":204943,"text":"and my own continent of Africa."},{"time":207625,"text":"I've met with presidents, dissidents,"},{"time":210265,"text":"policymakers, lawyers, teachers,"},{"time":212633,"text":"doctors and the man on the street,"},{"time":214936,"text":"and through these conversations,"},{"time":216619,"text":"it's become clear to me"},{"time":218419,"text":"that many people in the emerging markets"},{"time":220347,"text":"believe that there's actually a split occurring"},{"time":223556,"text":"between what people believe ideologically"},{"time":226322,"text":"in terms of politics and economics in the West"},{"time":229008,"text":"and that which people believe in the rest of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231892,"text":"Now, don't get me wrong."},{"time":233763,"text":"I'm not saying people in the emerging markets"},{"time":235223,"text":"don't understand democracy,"},{"time":237314,"text":"nor am I saying that they wouldn't ideally"},{"time":239223,"text":"like to pick their presidents or their leaders."},{"time":241708,"text":"Of course they would."},{"time":243263,"text":"However, I am saying that on balance,"},{"time":246284,"text":"they worry more about"},{"time":247866,"text":"where their living standard improvements are going to come from,"},{"time":250897,"text":"and how it is their governments can deliver for them,"},{"time":253180,"text":"than whether or not the government"},{"time":255085,"text":"was elected by democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258025,"text":"The fact of the matter"},{"time":260114,"text":"is that this has become a very poignant question"},{"time":262579,"text":"because there is for the first time in a long time"},{"time":264912,"text":"a real challenge to the Western ideological systems"},{"time":268482,"text":"of politics and economics,"},{"time":270636,"text":"and this is a system that is embodied by China."},{"time":273709,"text":"And rather than have private capitalism,\nthey have state capitalism."},{"time":277687,"text":"Instead of liberal democracy,\nthey have de-prioritized the democratic system."},{"time":281959,"text":"And they have also decided to prioritize"},{"time":284323,"text":"economic rights over political rights."},{"time":287980,"text":"I put it to you today that it is this system"},{"time":290829,"text":"that is embodied by China"},{"time":292674,"text":"that is gathering momentum amongst people"},{"time":294634,"text":"in the emerging markets as the system to follow,"},{"time":297722,"text":"because they believe increasingly"},{"time":299742,"text":"that it is the system"},{"time":301417,"text":"that will promise the best and fastest improvements"},{"time":304818,"text":"in living standards in the shortest period of time."},{"time":308429,"text":"If you will indulge me, I will spend a few moments"},{"time":311008,"text":"explaining to you first"},{"time":312830,"text":"why economically they've come to this belief."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316860,"text":"First of all, it's China's economic performance"},{"time":319686,"text":"over the past 30 years."},{"time":321728,"text":"She's been able to produce record economic growth"},{"time":324448,"text":"and meaningfully move many people out of poverty,"},{"time":328083,"text":"specifically putting a meaningful dent in poverty"},{"time":331262,"text":"by moving over 300 million people"},{"time":334076,"text":"out of indigence."},{"time":337334,"text":"It's not just in economics,"},{"time":339848,"text":"but it's also in terms of living standards."},{"time":342345,"text":"We see that in China, 28 percent of people"},{"time":345189,"text":"had secondary school access."},{"time":347012,"text":"Today, it's closer to 82 percent."},{"time":349389,"text":"So in its totality, economic improvement"},{"time":351984,"text":"has been quite significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354680,"text":"Second, China has been able"},{"time":357716,"text":"to meaningfully improve its income inequality"},{"time":360852,"text":"without changing the political construct."},{"time":363517,"text":"Today, the United States and China"},{"time":365947,"text":"are the two leading economies in the world."},{"time":368473,"text":"They have vastly different political systems"},{"time":370722,"text":"and different economic systems,"},{"time":373044,"text":"one with private capitalism,"},{"time":374514,"text":"another one broadly with state capitalism."},{"time":376953,"text":"However, these two countries"},{"time":379026,"text":"have the identical GINI Coefficient,"},{"time":381133,"text":"which is a measure of income equality."},{"time":383680,"text":"Perhaps what is more disturbing"},{"time":385912,"text":"is that China's income equality"},{"time":388006,"text":"has been improving in recent times,"},{"time":390327,"text":"whereas that of the United States"},{"time":391944,"text":"has been declining."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395007,"text":"Thirdly, people in the emerging markets"},{"time":397563,"text":"look at China's amazing and legendary"},{"time":399957,"text":"infrastructure rollout."},{"time":402283,"text":"This is not just about China"},{"time":403942,"text":"building roads and ports and railways"},{"time":406302,"text":"in her own country --"},{"time":407738,"text":"she's been able to build 85,000 kilometers"},{"time":410826,"text":"of road network in China"},{"time":412417,"text":"and surpass that of the United States --"},{"time":415365,"text":"but even if you look to places like Africa,"},{"time":418176,"text":"China has been able to help tar the distance"},{"time":421233,"text":"of Cape Town to Cairo,"},{"time":422887,"text":"which is 9,000 miles,"},{"time":424512,"text":"or three times the distance of New York to California."},{"time":428423,"text":"Now this is something that people can see and point to."},{"time":432863,"text":"Perhaps it's no surprise"},{"time":434545,"text":"that in a 2007 Pew survey, when surveyed,"},{"time":438266,"text":"Africans in 10 countries said"},{"time":440134,"text":"they thought that the Chinese were doing"},{"time":441802,"text":"amazing things to improve their livelihoods"},{"time":443696,"text":"by wide margins, by as much as 98 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448194,"text":"Finally, China is also providing innovative solutions"},{"time":452714,"text":"to age-old social problems that the world faces."},{"time":456085,"text":"If you travel to Mogadishu, Mexico City or Mumbai,"},{"time":459353,"text":"you find that dilapidated infrastructure and logistics"},{"time":462605,"text":"continue to be a stumbling block"},{"time":464832,"text":"to the delivery of medicine and healthcare"},{"time":466933,"text":"in the rural areas."},{"time":468803,"text":"However, through a network of state-owned enterprises,"},{"time":471681,"text":"the Chinese have been able to go into these rural areas,"},{"time":474577,"text":"using their companies"},{"time":476067,"text":"to help deliver on these healthcare solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479339,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, it's no surprise"},{"time":481545,"text":"that around the world, people are pointing\nat what China is doing and saying,"},{"time":484795,"text":"\"I like that. I want that."},{"time":486937,"text":"I want to be able to do what China's doing."},{"time":489131,"text":"That is the system that seems to work.\""},{"time":491901,"text":"I'm here to also tell you"},{"time":493574,"text":"that there are lots of shifts occurring"},{"time":495321,"text":"around what China is doing"},{"time":497281,"text":"in the democratic stance."},{"time":499356,"text":"In particular, there is growing doubt"},{"time":502021,"text":"among people in the emerging markets,"},{"time":504123,"text":"when people now believe that democracy"},{"time":505830,"text":"is no longer to be viewed"},{"time":508114,"text":"as a prerequisite for economic growth."},{"time":511597,"text":"In fact, countries like Taiwan, Singapore, Chile,"},{"time":515838,"text":"not just China, have shown that actually,"},{"time":518746,"text":"it's economic growth that is a prerequisite"},{"time":521432,"text":"for democracy."},{"time":523196,"text":"In a recent study, the evidence has shown"},{"time":526442,"text":"that income is the greatest determinant"},{"time":528940,"text":"of how long a democracy can last."},{"time":531688,"text":"The study found that if your per capita income"},{"time":534421,"text":"is about 1,000 dollars a year,"},{"time":536633,"text":"your democracy will last about eight and a half years."},{"time":539631,"text":"If your per capita income is between"},{"time":541349,"text":"2,000 and 4,000 dollars per year,"},{"time":543749,"text":"then you're likely to only get 33 years of democracy."},{"time":546791,"text":"And only if your per capita income"},{"time":548615,"text":"is above 6,000 dollars a year"},{"time":550746,"text":"will you have democracy come hell or high water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554490,"text":"What this is telling us"},{"time":556202,"text":"is that we need to first establish a middle class"},{"time":558775,"text":"that is able to hold the government accountable."},{"time":561892,"text":"But perhaps it's also telling us"},{"time":564267,"text":"that we should be worried about going"},{"time":565849,"text":"around the world and shoehorning democracy,"},{"time":568759,"text":"because ultimately we run the risk"},{"time":570569,"text":"of ending up with illiberal democracies,"},{"time":572699,"text":"democracies that in some sense"},{"time":574760,"text":"could be worse than the authoritarian governments"},{"time":576927,"text":"that they seek to replace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580614,"text":"The evidence around illiberal democracies"},{"time":582880,"text":"is quite depressing."},{"time":584700,"text":"Freedom House finds that although 50 percent"},{"time":587146,"text":"of the world's countries today are democratic,"},{"time":590303,"text":"70 percent of those countries are illiberal"},{"time":593009,"text":"in the sense that people don't have free speech"},{"time":595362,"text":"or freedom of movement."},{"time":598107,"text":"But also, we're finding from Freedom House"},{"time":600426,"text":"in a study that they published last year"},{"time":602547,"text":"that freedom has been on the decline"},{"time":604662,"text":"every year for the past seven years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607234,"text":"What this says"},{"time":609018,"text":"is that for people like me"},{"time":610356,"text":"who care about liberal democracy,"},{"time":612966,"text":"is we've got to find a more sustainable way"},{"time":615313,"text":"of ensuring that we have a sustainable form"},{"time":617658,"text":"of democracy in a liberal way,"},{"time":619859,"text":"and that has its roots in economics."},{"time":622859,"text":"But it also says that as China moves"},{"time":625788,"text":"toward being the largest economy in the world,"},{"time":628320,"text":"something that is expected to happen"},{"time":630341,"text":"by experts in 2016,"},{"time":632416,"text":"that this schism between the political"},{"time":634686,"text":"and economic ideologies of the West and the rest"},{"time":638048,"text":"is likely to widen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640979,"text":"What might that world look like?"},{"time":643534,"text":"Well, the world could look like"},{"time":645096,"text":"more state involvement and state capitalism;"},{"time":648361,"text":"greater protectionisms of nation-states;"},{"time":651200,"text":"but also, as I just pointed out a moment ago,"},{"time":653709,"text":"ever-declining political rights"},{"time":655876,"text":"and individual rights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657937,"text":"The question that is left for us in general"},{"time":660699,"text":"is, what then should the West be doing?"},{"time":663815,"text":"And I suggest that they have two options."},{"time":666520,"text":"The West can either compete or cooperate."},{"time":670937,"text":"If the West chooses to compete with the Chinese model,"},{"time":674125,"text":"and in effect go around the world"},{"time":676132,"text":"and continue to try and push an agenda"},{"time":678459,"text":"of private capitalism and liberal democracy,"},{"time":681499,"text":"this is basically going against headwinds,"},{"time":684155,"text":"but it also would be a natural stance"},{"time":686179,"text":"for the West to take"},{"time":687640,"text":"because in many ways it is the antithesis"},{"time":689673,"text":"of the Chinese model"},{"time":691820,"text":"of de-prioritizing democracy, and state capitalism."},{"time":695948,"text":"Now the fact of the matter is,"},{"time":697727,"text":"if the West decides to compete,"},{"time":699685,"text":"it will create a wider schism."},{"time":703083,"text":"The other option is for the West to cooperate,"},{"time":705936,"text":"and by cooperating I mean"},{"time":707530,"text":"giving the emerging market countries the flexibility"},{"time":711040,"text":"to figure out in an organic way"},{"time":713087,"text":"what political and economic system"},{"time":714849,"text":"works best for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716542,"text":"Now I'm sure some of you in the room"},{"time":718272,"text":"will be thinking, well, this is like ceding to China,"},{"time":721146,"text":"and this is a way, in other words,"},{"time":723217,"text":"for the West to take a back seat."},{"time":725129,"text":"But I put it to you"},{"time":726584,"text":"that if the United States and European countries"},{"time":728934,"text":"want to remain globally influential,"},{"time":731585,"text":"they may have to consider cooperating"},{"time":733455,"text":"in the short term in order to compete,"},{"time":736004,"text":"and by that, they might have to focus"},{"time":738247,"text":"more aggressively on economic outcomes"},{"time":741482,"text":"to help create the middle class"},{"time":743191,"text":"and therefore be able to hold government accountable"},{"time":745862,"text":"and create the democracies that we really want."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749889,"text":"The fact of the matter is that"},{"time":752478,"text":"instead of going around the world"},{"time":754381,"text":"and haranguing countries for engaging with China,"},{"time":757868,"text":"the West should be encouraging its own businesses"},{"time":760828,"text":"to trade and invest in these regions."},{"time":763327,"text":"Instead of criticizing China for bad behavior,"},{"time":767579,"text":"the West should be showing how it is"},{"time":770179,"text":"that their own system of politics and economics"},{"time":772566,"text":"is the superior one."},{"time":774716,"text":"And instead of shoehorning democracy"},{"time":776736,"text":"around the world,"},{"time":778227,"text":"perhaps the West should take a leaf"},{"time":779502,"text":"out of its own history book"},{"time":781354,"text":"and remember that it takes a lot of patience"},{"time":784204,"text":"in order to develop the models"},{"time":785774,"text":"and the systems that you have today."},{"time":788107,"text":"Indeed, the Supreme Court Justice Stephen Breyer"},{"time":791579,"text":"reminds us that it took the United States"},{"time":794208,"text":"nearly 170 years"},{"time":796854,"text":"from the time that the Constitution was written"},{"time":799523,"text":"for there to be equal rights in the United States."},{"time":802483,"text":"Some people would argue that today"},{"time":803845,"text":"there is still no equal rights."},{"time":805359,"text":"In fact, there are groups who would argue"},{"time":807205,"text":"that they still do not have equal rights under the law."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812533,"text":"At its very best,"},{"time":814115,"text":"the Western model speaks for itself."},{"time":816367,"text":"It's the model that put food on the table."},{"time":818528,"text":"It's the refrigerators."},{"time":820119,"text":"It put a man on the moon."},{"time":822151,"text":"But the fact of the matter is,"},{"time":823941,"text":"although people back in the day"},{"time":825591,"text":"used to point at the Western countries and say,"},{"time":827657,"text":"\"I want that, I like that,\""},{"time":829700,"text":"there's now a new person in town"},{"time":831859,"text":"in the form of a country, China."},{"time":834298,"text":"Today, generations are looking at China"},{"time":836384,"text":"and saying, \"China can produce infrastructure,"},{"time":839024,"text":"China can produce economic growth,"},{"time":841140,"text":"and we like that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":842708,"text":"Because ultimately, the question before us,"},{"time":845422,"text":"and the question before"},{"time":847278,"text":"seven billion people on the planet"},{"time":848983,"text":"is, how can we create prosperity?"},{"time":852083,"text":"People who care and will pivot towards the model"},{"time":854998,"text":"of politics and economics"},{"time":856523,"text":"in a very rational way,"},{"time":858090,"text":"to those models that will ensure"},{"time":860555,"text":"that they can have better living standards"},{"time":862536,"text":"in the shortest period of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865159,"text":"As you leave here today,"},{"time":866870,"text":"I would like to leave you"},{"time":868275,"text":"with a very personal message,"},{"time":869928,"text":"which is what it is that I believe"},{"time":872014,"text":"we should be doing as individuals,"},{"time":874418,"text":"and this is really about being open-minded,"},{"time":877787,"text":"open-minded to the fact that our hopes and dreams"},{"time":881126,"text":"of creating prosperity for people around the world,"},{"time":884361,"text":"creating and meaningfully putting a dent in poverty"},{"time":887285,"text":"for hundreds of millions of people,"},{"time":888961,"text":"has to be based in being open-minded,"},{"time":891745,"text":"because these systems have good things"},{"time":893972,"text":"and they have bad things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896449,"text":"Just to illustrate,"},{"time":898158,"text":"I went into my annals of myself."},{"time":900644,"text":"That's a picture of me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902426,"text":"Awww. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":904666,"text":"I was born and raised in Zambia in 1969."},{"time":908892,"text":"At the time of my birth,"},{"time":910839,"text":"blacks were not issued birth certificates,"},{"time":912921,"text":"and that law only changed in 1973."},{"time":915265,"text":"This is an affidavit from the Zambian government."},{"time":918410,"text":"I bring this to you to tell you that in 40 years,"},{"time":920862,"text":"I've gone from not being recognized as a human being"},{"time":923747,"text":"to standing in front of the illustrious TED crowd today"},{"time":926694,"text":"to talk to you about my views."},{"time":929272,"text":"In this vein, we can increase economic growth."},{"time":932996,"text":"We can meaningfully put a dent in poverty."},{"time":936413,"text":"But also, it's going to require"},{"time":938614,"text":"that we look at our assumptions,"},{"time":940608,"text":"assumptions and strictures that we've grown up with"},{"time":942835,"text":"around democracy, around private capitalism,"},{"time":944814,"text":"around what creates economic growth"},{"time":946749,"text":"and reduces poverty and creates freedoms."},{"time":949381,"text":"We might have to tear those books up"},{"time":951258,"text":"and start to look at other options"},{"time":953829,"text":"and be open-minded to seek the truth."},{"time":956686,"text":"Ultimately, it's about transforming the world"},{"time":958933,"text":"and making it a better place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960619,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962837,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}